methods.name: _pathGet
methods.description:
Reads a value from a path.  If any sub-property in the path is `undefined`,
this method returns `undefined` (will never throw.

params.name: root
params.description: Object from which to dereference path from

return.desc:
Value at path, or `undefined` if the path could not be
 fully dereferenced.

methods.name: _pathSet
methods.description:
Sets a value to a path.  If any sub-property in the path is `undefined`,
this method will no-op.

params.name: root
params.description: Object from which to dereference path from

return.desc: The normalized version of the input path

methods.name: _split
methods.description:
Splits a path into an array of property names. Accepts either arrays
of path parts or strings.

Example:

```
split(['foo.bar', 0, 'baz'])  // ['foo', 'bar', '0', 'baz']
split('foo.bar.0.baz')        // ['foo', 'bar', '0', 'baz']
```

return.desc: Array of path parts

Reads a value from a path.  If any sub-property in the path is `undefined`,
this method returns `undefined` (will never throw.

params.name: root
params.description: Object from which to dereference path from

return.desc:
Value at path, or `undefined` if the path could not be
 fully dereferenced.

methods.name: _pathSet
methods.description:
Sets a value to a path.  If any sub-property in the path is `undefined`,
this method will no-op.

params.name: root
params.description: Object from which to dereference path from

return.desc: The normalized version of the input path

methods.name: _split
methods.description:
Splits a path into an array of property names. Accepts either arrays
of path parts or strings.

Example:

```
split(['foo.bar', 0, 'baz'])  // ['foo', 'bar', '0', 'baz']
split('foo.bar.0.baz')        // ['foo', 'bar', '0', 'baz']
```

return.desc: Array of path parts

elements.description:
`furo-reference-search`
 Sucht eine Referenz


```
<!--  entity-object will eine Referenz aufl√∂sen -->
<entity-object type="vnd.com.acme.task" @-object-ready="--entityReady"></entity-object>

<furo-horizontal-flex>
   <!--  furo-reference-search kann eine Referenz die entity-objekt besitzt darstellen.
   Bei einer Texteingabe wird ^^search mit dem eingegebenen Text gesucht. Diesr geht via wire --term an den collection-agent.
   Wenn collection-agent eine Kollektion zur√ºckliefert, klappt die Auswahl auf. -->
   <furo-reference-search autofocus  flex ∆í-bind-data="--entityReady(*.fields.ref)" @-search="--term" ∆í-collection-in="--refCol"></furo-reference-search>

   <furo-reference-search  flex ∆í-bind-data="--entityReady(*.fields.ref)" min-term-length="2" @-search="--term" ∆í-collection-in="--refCol"></furo-reference-search>

</furo-horizontal-flex>

<!-- Der collection-agent erh√§lt die hts von ref.value, wenn ein term eingegeben wurde beginnt dieser zu suchen.
Die Resultate werden an furo-reference-search zur√ºck gegeben. -->
<collection-agent service="tasks" ∆í-search="--term" ∆í-hts-in="--entityReady(*.fields.ref.value)" @-response="--refCol"></collection-agent>

```
